Ext.data.JsonP['Widgets']({"guide":"<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\" ?>\n<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC \"-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Transitional//EN\"\n        \"http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-transitional.dtd\">\n<html xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\">\n<head>\n    <title>Widgets</title>\n\n    <meta http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html; charset=UTF-8\">\n    <meta content=\"Scroll EclipseHelp Exporter\" name=\"generator\">\n\n    <link type=\"text/css\" rel=\"stylesheet\">\n    <link type=\"text/css\" rel=\"stylesheet\">\n    <link type=\"text/css\" rel=\"stylesheet\" media=\"print\">\n</link></link></link></meta></meta></head>\n<body>\n    <div class=\"container\">\n\t\t<div id=\"banner\" class=\"confbox admonition admonition-note aui-message warning shadowed information-macro\">\n\t\t\t<p>You can now find Appcelerator documentation at <a href=\"https://docs.axway.com/\" target=\"_blank\">https://docs.axway.com/</a>. This site will be taken down in the near future.</p></div>\n        <div class=\"header\"/>\n\n        <div id=\"src-41845642\" class=\"content\">\n                        <h1>Widgets</h1>\n    <p>Samples in the widgets/ folder demonstrates how to create and use <a class=\"document-link \" href=\"#!/guide/Alloy_Widgets\">Alloy widgets,</a> which are self-contained Alloy components that can easily be shared.    </p>\n<ul class=\"childpages-macro \"><li class=\" \">    <p><a class=\"document-link \" href=\"#!/guide/Basic_Widget\">Basic Widget</a> &#x2014; Demonstrates how to create and use a basic widget.    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p><a class=\"document-link \" href=\"#!/guide/Complex_Widget\">Complex Widget</a> &#x2014; Demonstrates a widget using another widget.    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p><a class=\"document-link \" href=\"#!/guide/Widget_Models\">Widget Models</a> &#x2014; Demonstrates using data models with a widget.    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p><a class=\"document-link \" href=\"#!/guide/WPATH_Example\">WPATH Example</a> &#x2014; Demonstrates how to use the WPATH() macro to easily map image and library paths to the widget folder.    </p>\n</li></ul>    <p>You can find more Alloy widgets created by the community at <a class=\"external-link external-link\" href=\"http://gitt.io/\" target=\"_blank\">gitt.io/</a>.    </p>\n        </div><a id=\"editButton\" href=\"https://wiki.appcelerator.org/pages/editpage.action?pageId=41845642\"><span>Edit</span></a>\n    \n        \n    </div>\n</body>\n</html>\n","title":"Widgets"});